               <a href="/indices/xbx">
                XBX
               </a>
               <svg class="SvgIcon__StyledSvgIcon-sc-2tb2y8-0 jjONTr" data-for="xbx" data-tip="xbx" fill="#fff" height="24px" rotate="0" viewbox="0 0 24 24" width="24px">

                  <div class="mobile-layout">
                   <div class="tooltip-content">
                    <section>
                     <div class="decoration">
                     </div>
                     <h3 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 iKnOpn heading">
                      Bitcoin Price Index XBX
                     </h3>
                     <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 kJNyZX" color="rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55)"/>
                     <p class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bZvpZH desc">
                      The CoinDesk Bitcoin Price Index (XBX) is the world\xe2\x80\x99s leading reference for the price of bitcoin, used by the largest institutions active in crypto assets. It is the crypto market standard, benchmarking billions of dollars in registered financial products and pricing hundreds of millions in daily over-the-counter transactions. Built for replicability and reliability, in continuous operation since 2014, the XBX is relied upon by asset allocators, asset managers, market participants and exchanges. The XBX is the flagship in a
                      <!-- -->
                      <a href="/indices/xbx" style="color:#00D964">
                       portfolio of single- and multi-asset indices offered by CoinDesk.
                      </a>
                     </p>

            <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
             <div class="at-text about-transition">
              <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
               <p>
                The Bitcoin price is $23,110.93, a change of -0.27% over the past 24 hours as of 1:36 a.m.  The recent price action in Bitcoin left the tokens market capitalization at $446,061,228,457.52. So far this year, Bitcoin has a change of 40.20%. Bitcoin is classified as a Currency under CoinDesks Digital Asset Classification Standard (DACS).
               </p>
               <br/>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="styled-wrapperstyles__AboutSectionWrapper-ck3kmf-1 iuaYRZ">
              <div>
               <div class="contentstyle__StyledWrapper-g5cdrh-0 jsJHBz" data-submodule-name="composer-content">
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin is the world\xe2\x80\x99s first decentralized cryptocurrency \xe2\x80\x93 a type of digital asset that uses
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/how-public-key-infrastructure-will-revolutionize-custody-and-fund-management/">
                    public-key cryptography
                   </a>
                   to record, sign and send transactions over the Bitcoin
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-blockchain-technology/">
                    blockchain
                   </a>
                   \xe2\x80\x93 all done without the oversight of a central authority.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   The
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-bitcoin/" target="_blank">
                    Bitcoin
                   </a>
                   network (with an upper-case \xe2\x80\x9cB\xe2\x80\x9d) was launched in January 2009 by an anonymous computer programmer or group of programmers under the pseudonym \xe2\x80\x9cSatoshi Nakamoto.\xe2\x80\x9d The network is a peer-to-peer electronic payment system that uses a cryptocurrency called bitcoin (lower case \xe2\x80\x9cb\xe2\x80\x9d) to transfer value over the internet or act as a store of value like gold and silver.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Each bitcoin is made up of 100 million
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-a-satoshi-understanding-the-smallest-unit-of-bitcoin/" target="_blank">
                    satoshis
                   </a>
                   (the smallest units of bitcoin), making individual bitcoin divisible up to eight decimal places. That means anyone can purchase a fraction of a bitcoin with as little as one U.S. dollar.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Bitcoin price
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price is renowned for being highly volatile, but despite that, it has become the
                   <a href="https://twitter.com/charliebilello/status/1370722188739891202?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1370722188739891202%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fcointelegraph.com%2Fnews%2Fbtc-was-best-performing-asset-of-past-decade-by-900">
                    top performing asset
                   </a>
                   of any class (including stocks, commodities and bonds) over the past decade \xe2\x80\x93 climbing a staggering 9,000,000% between 2010 and 2020.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   When the cryptocurrency was launched at the beginning of 2009, as Satoshi Nakamoto mined the bitcoin genesis block (the first-ever block on the Bitcoin blockchain), 50 BTC entered circulation at a price of $0.00.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Fifty bitcoin continued to enter circulation every block (created once every 10 minutes) until the first halving event took place in November 2012 (see below). Halvings refer to bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s issuance system, which was programmed into Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s code by Satoshi Nakamoto. It essentially involves automatically halving the number of new BTC entering circulation every 210,000 blocks.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In February 2011, BTC\xe2\x80\x99s price reached parity with the U.S dollar for the first time. The milestone encouraged new investors into the market, and over the next four months, bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price continued to rise \xe2\x80\x93 peaking at over $30.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   By early 2013, the leading cryptocurrency had recovered from a prolonged bearish episode and rose above $1,000, albeit only briefly. But with the infamous
                   <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mt._Gox">
                    Mt Gox hack
                   </a>
                   , China announcing its first ban on crypto and other situations, it took a further four years for the BTC price to return to above $1,000 again. Once that level was passed, however, bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price continued to surge dramatically throughout 2017 until BTC peaked at its previous
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2020/11/30/bitcoin-price-sets-new-record-high-of-19850/">
                    long-standing all-time high of $19,850
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Over 2018, the entire crypto market plunged into what is now known as the \xe2\x80\x9ccrypto winter\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 a yearlong bear market. It wasn\xe2\x80\x99t until December 2020, when bitcoin returned to test the previous all-time high, that it eventually surpassed that historical level and rose a further 239% over the next 119 days to a new all-time high of $64,799.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   How does Bitcoin work?
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies are like the email of the financial world. The currency doesn\xe2\x80\x99t exist in a physical form, and the coin is transacted directly between the sender and the receiver without banking intermediaries to facilitate the transaction. Everything is done publicly through a transparent, immutable, distributed ledger technology called
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/blockchain-101/how-does-blockchain-technology-work/">
                    blockchain
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="liststyles__StyledWrapper-sc-13iatdm-0 fQjgTt">
                 <div class="at-list">
                  <ul class="\n">
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Here are the main features of blockchain technology:
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin transactions are recorded on a public, distributed ledger known as a \xe2\x80\x9cblockchain\xe2\x80\x9d that anyone can download and help maintain.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Transactions are sent directly from the sender to the receiver without any intermediaries.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Holders who store their own bitcoin have complete control over it. It cannot be accessed without the holder\xe2\x80\x99s cryptographic key.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin doesn\xe2\x80\x99t exist in a physical form.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin has a fixed supply of 21 million. No more bitcoin can be created and units of bitcoin cannot be destroyed.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin users send and receive coins over the network by inputting the public-key information attached to each person\xe2\x80\x99s digital wallet.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In order to incentivize the distributed network of people verifying bitcoin transactions (miners), a fee is attached to each transaction. The fee is awarded to whichever miner adds the transaction to a new block. Fees work on a first-price auction system, where the higher the fee attached to the transaction, the more likely a miner will process that transaction first.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Every single bitcoin transaction that takes place has to be permanently committed to the Bitcoin blockchain ledger through a process called \xe2\x80\x9cmining.\xe2\x80\x9d Bitcoin mining refers to the process where miners compete using specialized computer equipment known as application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) chips to unlock the next block in the chain.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Unlocking blocks work as follows:
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="liststyles__StyledWrapper-sc-13iatdm-0 fQjgTt">
                 <div class="at-list">
                  <ul class="\n">
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Crypto mining uses a system called cryptographic
                     <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/what-does-hashrate-mean/">
                      hashing
                     </a>
                     . This function simply takes any input (messages, words or data of any kind) and turns it into a fixed-length alphanumeric code known as a \xe2\x80\x9chash.\xe2\x80\x9d
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Each input creates a completely unique hash, and it\xe2\x80\x99s almost impossible to predict what inputs will create certain hashes. Even changing one character of the input will result in a totally different fixed-length code.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Each new block has a value called a \xe2\x80\x9ctarget hash.\xe2\x80\x9d In order to win the right to fill the next block, miners need to produce a hash that is lower than or equal to the numeric value of the \xe2\x80\x98target\xe2\x80\x99 hash. Since hashes are completely random, it\xe2\x80\x99s just a matter of trial and error until one miner is successful.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   This method of requiring miners to use machines and spend time and energy trying to achieve something is known as a proof-of-work system and is designed to deter malicious agents from spamming or disrupting the network.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Whoever successfully unlocks the next block is rewarded with a set number of bitcoin known as \xe2\x80\x9cblock rewards\xe2\x80\x9d and gets to add a number of transactions to the new block. They also earn any transaction fees attached to the transactions they add to the new block. A new block is discovered roughly once every 10 minutes.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin block rewards decrease over time. Every 210,000 blocks, or about once every four years, the number of bitcoin received from each block reward is halved to gradually reduce the number of bitcoin entering the space over time. As of 2021, miners receive 6.25 bitcoins each time they mine a new block. The next bitcoin
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/bitcoin-halving-explainer/">
                    halving
                   </a>
                   is expected to occur in 2024 and will see bitcoin block rewards drop to 3.125 bitcoins per block. As the supply of new bitcoin entering the market gets smaller, it will make buying bitcoin more competitive \xe2\x80\x93 assuming demand for bitcoin remains high.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s energy consumption
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   The process of requiring network contributors to dedicate time and resources to creating new blocks ensures the network remains secure. But that security comes at a price. As of 2021, the Bitcoin network consumes about 93 terawatt hours (TWh) of electricity per year \xe2\x80\x93 around the same energy consumed by the 34th-largest country in the world.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   This appetite for electricity has drawn widespread criticism from celebrities such as Tesla CEO Elon Musk to government bodies such as China\xe2\x80\x99s State Council and the U.S. Senate over Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s impact on climate change. But while the electricity figures are alarmingly high, it\xe2\x80\x99s important to note that bitcoin mining at most accounts for 1.29% of any single country\xe2\x80\x99s energy consumption. Not to mention, Bitcoin is a complete financial system whose energy consumption can be measured and tracked, unlike the fiat system, which cannot be accurately measured and requires a range of additional layers to function, including ATMs, card machines, bank branches, security vehicles, storage facilities and huge data centers.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   There are also a number of initiatives including the Crypto Climate Accord and the Bitcoin Mining Council that aim to improve Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s carbon footprint by encouraging miners to use renewable sources of energy.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Management
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   As already mentioned, the Bitcoin network was created by a pseudonymous programmer, or group of programmers, known only as \xe2\x80\x9cSatoshi Nakamoto.\xe2\x80\x9d During its early development, other developers joined to work on the protocol, including cypherpunk Hal Finney, cryptographers Wei Dai and Nick Szabo and software developer Gavin Andresen.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   There were also a range of other developers including Pieter Wuille and Peter Todd who contributed to the development of Bitcoin Core \xe2\x80\x93 the first client on the Bitcoin network. A client is a piece of software that enables a network participant to run a node and connect to the blockchain.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   An American nonprofit called the Bitcoin Foundation was founded in 2012 to support the development and adoption of the Bitcoin protocol. After three years, however, the foundation eventually ran out of cash and was dissolved.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In 2014, Adam Back, another cypherpunk and the inventor of Hashcash \xe2\x80\x93 a cryptographic hashing algorithm created in 1997 which used the same proof-of-work mechanism that Bitcoin would later adopt \xe2\x80\x93 co-founded Blockstream. Blockstream is a for-profit tech company that develops new infrastructure on the Bitcoin network, including Lightning Network and sidechains.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-block">
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
               <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>

This comes as developer James O'Beirne is warning that the dominant blockchain might lose some very talented contributors if someone doesn\xe2\x80\x99t step up to pay them for their work.             </span>
           </div>
          </div>

             21.00M
            </span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 jmSlhl">
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 coOxjX" display="flex">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
             24H Value Transacted
            </span>
            <svg class="SvgIcon__StyledSvgIcon-sc-2tb2y8-0 XtFcC" data-for="24H Value Transacted" data-tip="true" height="14px" rotate="0" viewbox="0 0 24 24" width="14px">
             <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z">
             </path>
            </svg>
           </div>
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 ixCWib">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 gaZnSf">
             $4.35B
            </span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 gNODGm">
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 snFAI" display="flex">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
             30D Volatility
            </span>
            <svg class="SvgIcon__StyledSvgIcon-sc-2tb2y8-0 XtFcC" data-for="30D Volatility" data-tip="true" height="14px" rotate="0" viewbox="0 0 24 24" width="14px">
             <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z">
             </path>
            </svg>
           </div>
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 ixCWib">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 gaZnSf">
             0.50902300
            </span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 jmSlhl">
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 coOxjX" display="flex">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
             24H Transaction Count
            </span>
            <svg class="SvgIcon__StyledSvgIcon-sc-2tb2y8-0 XtFcC" data-for="24H Transaction Count" data-tip="true" height="14px" rotate="0" viewbox="0 0 24 24" width="14px">
             <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z">
             </path>
            </svg>
           </div>
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 ixCWib">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 gaZnSf">
             298,377
            </span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 gNODGm">
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 snFAI" display="flex">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
             24H Average Transaction Fee
            </span>
            <svg class="SvgIcon__StyledSvgIcon-sc-2tb2y8-0 XtFcC" data-for="24H Average Transaction Fee" data-tip="true" height="14px" rotate="0" viewbox="0 0 24 24" width="14px">
             <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z">
             </path>
            </svg>
           </div>
           <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 ixCWib">
            <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 gaZnSf">
             $1.46
            </span>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dskahF">
          <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
         </div>
         <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-block display-mobile-block">
          <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 DkqkW">
           <div class="styled-wrapperstyles__StyledWrapper-ck3kmf-0 jeaRjJ">
            <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
             <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 dnMwjB">
              About
              <!-- -->
              Bitcoin
             </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 hgrchE" display="grid">
             <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 bWliNl">
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 VkmGE" display="grid,block,block">
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
                  Sector
                 </span>
                </div>
               </div>
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 keDxjI">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <p class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 kzGyYF mobile-right-alignment">
                  Currency
                 </p>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
               <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-block">
                <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 bWliNl">
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 VkmGE" display="grid,block,block">
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <h1 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
                  Industry Group
                 </h1>
                </div>
               </div>
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 keDxjI">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <p class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 kzGyYF mobile-right-alignment">
                  Transparent
                 </p>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
               <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-block">
                <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 bWliNl">
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 VkmGE" display="grid,block,block">
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <span class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 fUOSEs">
                  Industry
                 </span>
                </div>
               </div>
               <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 keDxjI">
                <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 dThFWu" display="flex">
                 <p class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 kzGyYF mobile-right-alignment">
                  Transparent (DeFi Currency)
                 </p>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
               <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-block">
                <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
             <div class="display-desktop-block display-tablet-block display-mobile-none">
              <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
             <div class="at-text about-transition">
              <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
               <p>
                The Bitcoin price is $23,110.93, a change of -0.27% over the past 24 hours as of 1:36 a.m.  The recent price action in Bitcoin left the tokens market capitalization at $446,061,228,457.52. So far this year, Bitcoin has a change of 40.20%. Bitcoin is classified as a Currency under CoinDesks Digital Asset Classification Standard (DACS).
               </p>
               <br/>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="styled-wrapperstyles__AboutSectionWrapper-ck3kmf-1 iuaYRZ">
              <div>
               <div class="contentstyle__StyledWrapper-g5cdrh-0 jsJHBz" data-submodule-name="composer-content">
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin is the world\xe2\x80\x99s first decentralized cryptocurrency \xe2\x80\x93 a type of digital asset that uses
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/how-public-key-infrastructure-will-revolutionize-custody-and-fund-management/">
                    public-key cryptography
                   </a>
                   to record, sign and send transactions over the Bitcoin
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-blockchain-technology/">
                    blockchain
                   </a>
                   \xe2\x80\x93 all done without the oversight of a central authority.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   The
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-bitcoin/" target="_blank">
                    Bitcoin
                   </a>
                   network (with an upper-case \xe2\x80\x9cB\xe2\x80\x9d) was launched in January 2009 by an anonymous computer programmer or group of programmers under the pseudonym \xe2\x80\x9cSatoshi Nakamoto.\xe2\x80\x9d The network is a peer-to-peer electronic payment system that uses a cryptocurrency called bitcoin (lower case \xe2\x80\x9cb\xe2\x80\x9d) to transfer value over the internet or act as a store of value like gold and silver.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Each bitcoin is made up of 100 million
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-a-satoshi-understanding-the-smallest-unit-of-bitcoin/" target="_blank">
                    satoshis
                   </a>
                   (the smallest units of bitcoin), making individual bitcoin divisible up to eight decimal places. That means anyone can purchase a fraction of a bitcoin with as little as one U.S. dollar.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Bitcoin price
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price is renowned for being highly volatile, but despite that, it has become the
                   <a href="https://twitter.com/charliebilello/status/1370722188739891202?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1370722188739891202%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fcointelegraph.com%2Fnews%2Fbtc-was-best-performing-asset-of-past-decade-by-900">
                    top performing asset
                   </a>
                   of any class (including stocks, commodities and bonds) over the past decade \xe2\x80\x93 climbing a staggering 9,000,000% between 2010 and 2020.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   When the cryptocurrency was launched at the beginning of 2009, as Satoshi Nakamoto mined the bitcoin genesis block (the first-ever block on the Bitcoin blockchain), 50 BTC entered circulation at a price of $0.00.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Fifty bitcoin continued to enter circulation every block (created once every 10 minutes) until the first halving event took place in November 2012 (see below). Halvings refer to bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s issuance system, which was programmed into Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s code by Satoshi Nakamoto. It essentially involves automatically halving the number of new BTC entering circulation every 210,000 blocks.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In February 2011, BTC\xe2\x80\x99s price reached parity with the U.S dollar for the first time. The milestone encouraged new investors into the market, and over the next four months, bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price continued to rise \xe2\x80\x93 peaking at over $30.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   By early 2013, the leading cryptocurrency had recovered from a prolonged bearish episode and rose above $1,000, albeit only briefly. But with the infamous
                   <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mt._Gox">
                    Mt Gox hack
                   </a>
                   , China announcing its first ban on crypto and other situations, it took a further four years for the BTC price to return to above $1,000 again. Once that level was passed, however, bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s price continued to surge dramatically throughout 2017 until BTC peaked at its previous
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2020/11/30/bitcoin-price-sets-new-record-high-of-19850/">
                    long-standing all-time high of $19,850
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Over 2018, the entire crypto market plunged into what is now known as the \xe2\x80\x9ccrypto winter\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 a yearlong bear market. It wasn\xe2\x80\x99t until December 2020, when bitcoin returned to test the previous all-time high, that it eventually surpassed that historical level and rose a further 239% over the next 119 days to a new all-time high of $64,799.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   How does Bitcoin work?
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies are like the email of the financial world. The currency doesn\xe2\x80\x99t exist in a physical form, and the coin is transacted directly between the sender and the receiver without banking intermediaries to facilitate the transaction. Everything is done publicly through a transparent, immutable, distributed ledger technology called
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/blockchain-101/how-does-blockchain-technology-work/">
                    blockchain
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="liststyles__StyledWrapper-sc-13iatdm-0 fQjgTt">
                 <div class="at-list">
                  <ul class="\n">
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Here are the main features of blockchain technology:
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin transactions are recorded on a public, distributed ledger known as a \xe2\x80\x9cblockchain\xe2\x80\x9d that anyone can download and help maintain.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Transactions are sent directly from the sender to the receiver without any intermediaries.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Holders who store their own bitcoin have complete control over it. It cannot be accessed without the holder\xe2\x80\x99s cryptographic key.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin doesn\xe2\x80\x99t exist in a physical form.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin has a fixed supply of 21 million. No more bitcoin can be created and units of bitcoin cannot be destroyed.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Bitcoin users send and receive coins over the network by inputting the public-key information attached to each person\xe2\x80\x99s digital wallet.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In order to incentivize the distributed network of people verifying bitcoin transactions (miners), a fee is attached to each transaction. The fee is awarded to whichever miner adds the transaction to a new block. Fees work on a first-price auction system, where the higher the fee attached to the transaction, the more likely a miner will process that transaction first.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Every single bitcoin transaction that takes place has to be permanently committed to the Bitcoin blockchain ledger through a process called \xe2\x80\x9cmining.\xe2\x80\x9d Bitcoin mining refers to the process where miners compete using specialized computer equipment known as application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) chips to unlock the next block in the chain.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Unlocking blocks work as follows:
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="liststyles__StyledWrapper-sc-13iatdm-0 fQjgTt">
                 <div class="at-list">
                  <ul class="\n">
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Crypto mining uses a system called cryptographic
                     <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/what-does-hashrate-mean/">
                      hashing
                     </a>
                     . This function simply takes any input (messages, words or data of any kind) and turns it into a fixed-length alphanumeric code known as a \xe2\x80\x9chash.\xe2\x80\x9d
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Each input creates a completely unique hash, and it\xe2\x80\x99s almost impossible to predict what inputs will create certain hashes. Even changing one character of the input will result in a totally different fixed-length code.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON">
                     Each new block has a value called a \xe2\x80\x9ctarget hash.\xe2\x80\x9d In order to win the right to fill the next block, miners need to produce a hash that is lower than or equal to the numeric value of the \xe2\x80\x98target\xe2\x80\x99 hash. Since hashes are completely random, it\xe2\x80\x99s just a matter of trial and error until one miner is successful.
                    </div>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   This method of requiring miners to use machines and spend time and energy trying to achieve something is known as a proof-of-work system and is designed to deter malicious agents from spamming or disrupting the network.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Whoever successfully unlocks the next block is rewarded with a set number of bitcoin known as \xe2\x80\x9cblock rewards\xe2\x80\x9d and gets to add a number of transactions to the new block. They also earn any transaction fees attached to the transactions they add to the new block. A new block is discovered roughly once every 10 minutes.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   Bitcoin block rewards decrease over time. Every 210,000 blocks, or about once every four years, the number of bitcoin received from each block reward is halved to gradually reduce the number of bitcoin entering the space over time. As of 2021, miners receive 6.25 bitcoins each time they mine a new block. The next bitcoin
                   <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/bitcoin-halving-explainer/">
                    halving
                   </a>
                   is expected to occur in 2024 and will see bitcoin block rewards drop to 3.125 bitcoins per block. As the supply of new bitcoin entering the market gets smaller, it will make buying bitcoin more competitive \xe2\x80\x93 assuming demand for bitcoin remains high.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s energy consumption
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   The process of requiring network contributors to dedicate time and resources to creating new blocks ensures the network remains secure. But that security comes at a price. As of 2021, the Bitcoin network consumes about 93 terawatt hours (TWh) of electricity per year \xe2\x80\x93 around the same energy consumed by the 34th-largest country in the world.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   This appetite for electricity has drawn widespread criticism from celebrities such as Tesla CEO Elon Musk to government bodies such as China\xe2\x80\x99s State Council and the U.S. Senate over Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s impact on climate change. But while the electricity figures are alarmingly high, it\xe2\x80\x99s important to note that bitcoin mining at most accounts for 1.29% of any single country\xe2\x80\x99s energy consumption. Not to mention, Bitcoin is a complete financial system whose energy consumption can be measured and tracked, unlike the fiat system, which cannot be accurately measured and requires a range of additional layers to function, including ATMs, card machines, bank branches, security vehicles, storage facilities and huge data centers.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   There are also a number of initiatives including the Crypto Climate Accord and the Bitcoin Mining Council that aim to improve Bitcoin\xe2\x80\x99s carbon footprint by encouraging miners to use renewable sources of energy.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="headingstyles__StyledWrapper-l955mv-0 fMEozb">
                 <div class="at-heading">
                  <h2 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 doaPpU">
                   Management
                  </h2>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   As already mentioned, the Bitcoin network was created by a pseudonymous programmer, or group of programmers, known only as \xe2\x80\x9cSatoshi Nakamoto.\xe2\x80\x9d During its early development, other developers joined to work on the protocol, including cypherpunk Hal Finney, cryptographers Wei Dai and Nick Szabo and software developer Gavin Andresen.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   There were also a range of other developers including Pieter Wuille and Peter Todd who contributed to the development of Bitcoin Core \xe2\x80\x93 the first client on the Bitcoin network. A client is a piece of software that enables a network participant to run a node and connect to the blockchain.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   An American nonprofit called the Bitcoin Foundation was founded in 2012 to support the development and adoption of the Bitcoin protocol. After three years, however, the foundation eventually ran out of cash and was dissolved.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="common-textstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-18pd49k-0 eSbCkN">
                 <div class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 bYmaON at-text">
                  <p>
                   In 2014, Adam Back, another cypherpunk and the inventor of Hashcash \xe2\x80\x93 a cryptographic hashing algorithm created in 1997 which used the same proof-of-work mechanism that Bitcoin would later adopt \xe2\x80\x93 co-founded Blockstream. Blockstream is a for-profit tech company that develops new infrastructure on the Bitcoin network, including Lightning Network and sidechains.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-block">
              <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 kXDJHA">
               <hr class="divider__StyledDivider-sc-149ljp0-0 dcwNIV dividerstyles__Divider-sc-196rq32-0 iBKgJM"/>
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0">
        <div class="vertstyles__StyledWrapper-sc-1qcdt5p-0 jqOjFT">
         <div class="Box-sc-1hpkeeg-0 vert">
          <div class="vert-content" id="" style="min-height:unset">
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>

           and the
           <a class="calculatorstyles__StyledLink-sc-14o78kh-8 dOAAZx" href="/coindesk20/">

           </a>

           <!-- -->

            Open Exchange Rates

                The January PCE Price Index \xe2\x80\x93 the Fed's favored inflation indicator \xe2\x80\x93 unexpectedly rose to 5.4%.

             <h6 class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 GgEdf">
              <a class="card-title" href="/markets/2023/02/24/bitcoin-futures-on-cme-trade-at-highest-premium-since-november-2021-binance-futures-lag/" target="_self">
               Bitcoin Futures on CME Outpace Those on Binance to Trade at Widest Premium Since November 2021
              </a>
             </h6>
             <div class="display-desktop-none display-tablet-none display-mobile-none">
              <p class="typography__StyledTypography-owin6q-0 lhbKMO">
               <span class="content-text">
                The CME accounts for a majority of activity in standard futures market tied to bitcoin, one observer said, while explaining a relatively higher premium in futures listed on the Chicago-based exchange.
               </span>
              </p>

         <!-- -->

         The leader in news and information on cryptocurrency, digital assets and the future of money, CoinDesk is a media outlet that strives for the highest journalistic standards and abides by a
         <!-- -->
         <a class="link__Link-lw0p1v-0 eXSyEc" href="/ethics/">
          strict set of editorial policies
         </a>
         .
         <!-- -->
         CoinDesk is an independent operating subsidiary of
         <!-- -->
         <a class="link__Link-lw0p1v-0 eXSyEc" href="https://dcg.co/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
          Digital Currency Group
         </a>
         ,
         <!-- -->
         which invests in
         <!-- -->
         <a class="link__Link-lw0p1v-0 eXSyEc" href="https://dcg.co/#digital-assets-portfolio" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">

         </a>
         .

layer 2 blockchain Base</b> had a rough start on Thursday, drawing a stream of complaints from users on social media. Plus, Coinbase software engineer Roberto Bayardo said that high demand from users overwhelmed the protocol. Back then, bitcoin traded at record highs near $69,000 \xe2\x80\x93 almost three times the current $24,850, <a href=\\"https://www.coindesk.com/price/bitcoin/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">CoinDesk data</a> shows. Futures typically trade at a premium in a sign of leverage being skewed on the bullish side when the underlying asset is appreciating in value. Conversely, during bear markets, discounts are often observed."},{"_id":"ZEIDVE7FSRBFPBFK7D5YXQXNTE","type":"text","additional_properties":{"_id":1677241516989,"comments":[],"inline_comments":[]},"content":"\\"The bull is back,\\" Arcane Research analyst Vetle Lunde told CoinDesk."},{"_id":"P7HGK4G4EFGZ7ASEPJNU7HUVSM","type":"header","level":2,"additional_properties":{"_id":1677239695708,"comments":[],"inline_comments":[]},"content":"CME takes the lead"},{"_id":"FUDI77WEKREBTKATK6LQTJTKTM","type":"text","additional_properties":{"_id":1677239695711,"comments":[],"inline_comments":[]},"content":"Historically, futures on the CME have traded at a relatively lower premium than those on Binance and other unregulated offshore entities, predominantly because these latter avenues offered higher leverage.
